President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Maine due to severe storms, flooding, and landslides that occurred from June 18 to July 8, 2009. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-4600.